    <item>
      <title>About Me</title>
      <link>https://jpughesanford.github.io/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://jpughesanford.github.io/about/</guid>
      <description>&lt;!-- &#xA;**I am currently seeking both Research Software Engineering positions and faculty positions at small liberal arts colleges. I am constraining my search to the Northeastern United States. Please feel free to reach out!**&#xA;--&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I am a Flatiron Research Fellow in the Center for Computational Neuroscience at the Simons Foundation. My research sits at the intersection of &lt;strong&gt;dynamical systems theory&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;machine learning&lt;/strong&gt;, with a focus on developing minimal models of complex processes. I am strongly motivated by the goal of making AI systems safer, more transparent, and easier to regulate.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
